properties.short_sum: Crashed due to mechanical failure while flying SAR for a 20-plane helilift southeast of Tam Ky.
Crashed 13 KM South of Gai Rai Village.
Crashed 6 KM North of Tien Phuoc.
This incident took place 14 KM South of Vinh Long Airfield.
Shot down and burned during SAR mission near the Plain of Jars.
Crewmember was KIA while supporting Hotel 2/4's insertion into LZ BLUE at BS692921.
Crashed in bad weather returning to Kham Duc. Had been the C&C and rescue ship for the first ever SHINING BRASS insertion.
While flying SOG RT Nevada from Kham Duc to Kontum, the tail boom folded inflight.
Hit by an RPG
Hit by an RPG during a host mission to rescue US Army soldiers.
Received multiple small arms hits and was forced to land.  CE died of wounds.
Hit by ground fire during resupply mission.
Lost both engines during medevac mission to SANCTUARY. All but one of the crew and some of the medevacs survived.
Shot down at 1845 hours killing pilot and seriously wounding the observer.  The observer was lifted out by a Shark aircraft.
This helicopter was shot down while attempting to extract part of a Nung Hatchet Force company on a SOG operation.
Pilot began disorientated in overcast and flew into a cliff.
Disintegrated in the air due to aft plyon structural failure while moving the aircraft and a med-evac to LPH-10.
Main rotor shot off by AAA.
Shot down during a "sniffer" mission.
Crashed into the Ky Lam River at BT001553, 7 KM S-SW Dien Ban.
MACV Recondo school training patrol extraction mission.
Aircraft accident, crashed into mountain during IFR flight.
May have overflown turn point on way to the OA. Shot down by heavy AW fire. Crashed and burned completely.
This aircraft is specifically mentioned as being damaged during the B-40 and satchel charge attack on Kontum Airfield.

Took hits in the tail rotor during a VR, crashed in the trees.
Shot down with 12 passengers and a crew of two.
Shot down while marking an enemy position for the gunships and airstrikes.
Destroyed by sapper attack that happened after midnight on that day making it 31 January 1968 when it was destroyed.
Crashed short of landing area during high density altitude and quartering tail wind conditions with gross weight.
Destroyed by sapper attack that happened before daylight on 31 January 1968.
Destroyed by sapper attack that happened before daylight on 31 January 1968.
Shot down by enemy .50 cal during night medevac for Army wounded.
Landed in unsecure LZ. Gunned down while walking toward Ceo Rio village with 3 Vietnamese including local commander W/ Roy E. Worth.
Reported overdue and missing at 1915H enroute to MMAF on an IFR clearance.
Shot down and crashed during Recon Team extraction. SSG Zabitosky won the Medal of Honor for rescuing the pilots.
Rescued crew from destroyed H-52.
After landing, hit by recoilless rifle round on the left side, bursted into flames, collapsed to the right and was completely destroyed.
Engine failed and aircraft crashed into the trees with Quang Duc Province Chief and American advisors as passengers.
Hit by enemy fire while returning for fuel at Kontum, lost tail rotor, crashed into trees, came to rest on left side. Was retrieved.
Believed to be hit by friendly mortar fire from base camp. Other members of the unit were watching from a bunker.
Shot down recovering a CCN team in Laos.
Crashed 3 miles from Da Nang during a medevac mission in bad weather.
Mid-air with #67-17255 during troop lift near Cheo Reo.
Lead B/229 AHB aircraft on the CA into the A Shau. Was hit by an enemy grenade, aborted the landing, tail boom separated, crashed.
This was Fosdick 5, maintenance chase ship for the 17th Avn Co. It was shot-down in marginal weather near A Luoi on a recovery mission.
Hit by an RPG and destroyed while landing CIDG reinforces at Ngok Tavak.
Received heavy AW fire during a BDA near Kontum. Crashed. Pilot died in LOH, observer died two years later.
Shot down while trying to rescue SGT Jackson from his downed LOH.
Crashed into mountain in bad weather while on a classified ordnance delivery mission.
Helicopter was forced down by enemy SA fire, crashed and rolled down a mountain.
Shot down while trying to rescue Marine A-4 on the Hellborn 215 mission.
While avoiding machine gun fire on climb out, collided with USAF FAC at about 1000 feet.  Both aircraft crashed.  The UH-1 burned.
While marking a small structure during a People Sniffer mission. Received extremely intense AW fire and crashed. Crew survived crash.
Believe this aircraft was BLUE 4 which was damaged after flying through debris from mid-air of BLUE 1 (66-16592) and the C&C (66-16601).
Believe this aircraft was BLUE 1 which had a mid-air with the C&C (66-16601). The debris also brought down BLUE 4 (66-16206).
Believe this was the 240th AHC C&C aircraft which had a mid-air with BLUE 1 (66-16592). The debris also brought down BLUE 4 (66-16206).
Took 24 hits while supporting MACV.
Mid-air with UH-1C 66-00740 during decent into an LZ, 4 injured on the Huey.
Crashed in the Vam Co Dong River 3 miles south of Ben Luc Bridge.
Hit in fuel cell by an RPG and crashed inverted.
Received a direct hit from a heavy artillery round while attempting to land and rescue MAJ Harvey Britt's downed crew. Aircraft burned.
This was Lt Goble's initial aircraft of the day.  Flown out of the zone with one engine after receiving heavy battle damage.
Aircraft crashed at 2055H in a heavily contested zone. This was Lt Goble's second aircraft of the day.
Was shot up in a single ship LZ, lifted off, crashed in the trees and burned.
Medivac shot down with one KIA.  The other crew members E & E and were picked up the next day.
Mid-air with AH-1G 67-15488 while returning from a Sniffer Mission along the Cambodian border.
Mid-air with UH-1C 66-15210 while returning from a Sniffer Mission along the Cambodian border.
Aircraft accident but details are unknown.
Involved in a mid-air with HMM-265 CH-46A #151917 near Hill 52, north of An Hoa.
Shot down while hovering in front of the Blue to check on their point man who had been shot.
LRRP insertion into a booby trapped LZ.  Three LRRPs and the CE killed.  The aircraft burned.
Received enemy fire, shot down, crashed, and burned while approaching the zone. Both pilots died of burns, both EM seriously injured.
Believed to be the 1 Cav helicopter in which SP4 Han died.
Shot down and destroyed by a group of VC during a BDA after a Cobra rocket attack during a VR mission.
Struck by hostile fire, crashed and burned.
Shot down and crashed during gun run on village near Cambodian border while covering ARVNs.
Hit by an RPG while landing in a hot LZ
This KINGBEE CH-34 was hit at altitude by a 37mm antiaircraft round and exploded.
While flying lead scout for 1/7th Cav Bn, received intense enemy fire, went inverted, crashed and exploded. Aircraft burned completely.
While on an armed recon at tree top level and 40 knots, the helicopter blew up and crashed.
Discovered and cornered a group of VC during a VR. Shot down and destroyed by the VC.
Crashed while supporting TACAN site in northern Laos
Received small arms fire, engine lost power, aircraft crashed and was damaged beyond economical repair.
Took hits during firing run, crashed hard and aircraft rolled on left side crushing CE. ARVNs helped roll A/C over to recover the body.
Experienced a Hughes Tail Spin in the AO, tree strike, and crashed.
Hit by RPG during an resupply mission.
This aircraft was destroyed in the ammo dump explosion at Dong Tam.
This aircraft was destroyed in the ammo dump explosion at Dong Tam.
This aircraft was destroyed in the ammo dump explosion at Dong Tam.
Taxi accident with 66-00914.
Shot down while repelling a LRRP and Engineering team in to cut a new LZ.
LOH hit by RPG.
Shot down during a VR west of Phan Thiet. Crashed and burned.
Took several 51 cal hits during VR west of Tam Ky that killed Huber. Did a running landing at Tam Ky.
Shot down while supporting ARVN troops in contact.
Hit by an unidentified type explosive round, crashed, killing all five passengers aboard.
Shot down by friendly artillery fire.
Crashed in the Gulf of Tonkin while attempting a pickup of a F-100 pilot.
Crashed after experiencing tail rotor failure.
Aircraft received small arms fire and 50 cal. causing the engine to catch on fire and the helicopter to crash. There were no casualties.
Engine failure on approach to LZ.
Shot down in the LZ on a night mission with two other slicks, two gun ships and C&C.
Caught in a cross fire during a VR near Lai Khe. Pilot hit 5 times, crashed and rolled.
Shot down during string extraction mission in Laos.
Shot down by NVA firing AKs at very close range.
Crashed in bay 8 KM W-NW of Chu Lai Airfield.
Tail rotor hit by small arms fire causing the loss of anti-torque control which resulted in a spin and crash while looking for Watkins.
After making repeated contact with the VC and reporting that the Observer was hit bad, the aircraft exploded in mid-air.

Crashed into tall trees after experiencing a tail rotor failure that may have resulted from enemy SA fire. Burned and exploded.
Hit by small arms fire, resulting in loss of power at a low altitude above thick jungle canopy.
Rotor wash picked up rubber membrane that bent stabilizer into tail rotor. Tail rotor failure. Spinning aircraft struck revetment.
Crashed while attempting to lift out a deer they had shot for a "Christmas meal."
Crashed in the Mekong River.
Downed by enemy fire during a gun run supporting TIGER SURPRISE on a night mission.
Dropped from US Army Crane when cable failed near Da Nang.
Pilot was shot in the head and the helicopter took several hits then crashed. Blues rescued the badly wounded pilot and observer.
After an explosion from within the ship, control was lost and the aircraft turned over on its right side.  The gunner was trapped.
Aircraft crashed at V (Vientiane) Pad when the pilot allowed the rotor RPM to get too low while overloaded for the altitude.
Shot down at night while looking to see if there were any survivors from 65-12885.  Three crew members picked up with one KIA.
Destroy by enemy fire during a resupply/medevac mission to a Hatchet Force company during HALFBACK.
Lost power during extraction.
Crashed in the ocean while serving as a chase for a VIP Huey. One Gunner survived
Destroyed by a satchel charge at Flanders Field, Dong Ba Thin, RVN on 3/7/70.
Crashed in the jungle and destroyed while support LRRP mission. Suspect enemy ground fire caused the crash.
Shot down during a training flight in a free fire area.
Was shot down during a VR mission east and south of Dak To.
Enemy fire caused fire and aircraft was destroyed after successful forced landing.
Sources indicate to the VHPA that this was the aircraft in which these 119th KIAs were flying. Details, please contact the VHPA.
Helicopter hit by small arms fire on liftoff from an LZ causing the tail rotor to hit a tree which caused the helicopter to crash.
Shot down almost immediately after crossing into Cambodia. Observer died immediately. Pilot rescued.
Shot down near LZ Gypsy 14 KM W-SW of Pleiku City with a camera crew on board.
Engine failure 1 KM southwest of Mo Duc Airfield.
Shot down in a quad 50 trap. The entire crew of four was killed.
Received between 10 and 20 rounds of small arms fire, crashed and burned.  FO survived.
Shot down by ARVN 105 fire while relocating troops from the 47th ARVN Regt to a new LZ.
Shot down by enemy fire with Infantry troops on board. Crashed and burned in some water.
Shot down in flames while attempting to medevac SGT McMahan. All the crew managed to escape but SP4 Lamborn was killed outside.
Experience broken transmission strap while avoiding hostile fire, then an engine failure.
Shot down while support an ARVN troop relocation.
Destroyed by enemy mortar fire while sitting in LZ Nutmeg.
Crashed during night ARA mission possibly due to vertigo or target fixation.
Weather trapped Dustoff and 2 gunship escort in a valley. All went IFR. This ship crashed into the side of a hill.
LOH took intense fire when CPT Speare was given Scout orientation to Dickus. LOH crashed and burned.
Shot down at FSB Ripcord during MEDIVAC mission.  RPG blew off tail boom.
Aircraft accident during maintenance check.
Crash during a gun training mission. Recovery revealed bullet holes and possible engine failure.
Shot down during an SAR mission.
Crashed near the Thien Duc bridge in the Chau Thanh district while on an ARVN medevac mission.
Crashed at the mouth of the Ming Yang Pass 4 KM East of Phu Yen Village on QL-19.
Shot down and crashed inverted.  The Huey 67-17768 that tried to rescue them also got shot down killing two.
Rolled in on a 14.5 AAA after a Scout took fire. Took hits and caught fire at 500 ft AGL. Crashed hard and burned.
Shot down on take off by automatic weapons and B40 fire after picking up a wounded LT from an LZ east of Snuffy.
Scout mission on Laos border in SVN took fire from large enemy force, tried to stretch autorotation and ran out of RPM, crashed & burned
During a troop insertion in northern Laos, lost one engine due to hostile fire, FEs bailed out, pilots died in crash.
The main rotor head was blown off by .51 cal fire.
Mid-air with an Air America fixed wing that hit the Cobra from above and behind.
Believed to be the B/2/17th Cav Huey shot down in a ridge in the A Shau Valley in which CPTs Collum and Speidel died.
Lead Cobra of the Stand-by gun team at Camp Holloway. Shot down about 2130 hours while searching for survivors from two VNAF aircraft.
Pilot lost control of the aircraft in a crosswind condition and crashed into tall trees.
These three men were killed by an enemy rocket while working on this helicopter on the ground.
Ship crashed possibly due to hostile fire or pulling out of a gun run too low to clear the trees.
Helicopter was hit by an RPG round at a 50 foot hover, crashed and burned.
Returning from mission flying at altitude along the DMZ, A/C flew thru GT line of 122 rocket.  A/C exploded.
Believed to be a main rotor blade separate during a ferry flight.
Shot down in flames while doing a recon in Cambodia.  Pilots picked up by the C&C Huey 70-15737 flown by CPT Campbell.
Shot down by 51-cal that destroyed the tail rotor.
Crashed and burst into flames after experiencing an engine failure at low level while starting a Night Hawk mission over Cam Ranh Bay.
Hit by enemy fire during gun run near Loc Ninh. Tail boom separated while attempting to land.
Shot down by enemy fire.  Crew was killed in cockpit by enemy fire before they could get out.
Recon mission southwest of Pleiku against reported NVA brigade. 8 mm arms fire, crashed & burned. Last words "taking fire, taking fire!"
Shot down during extraction of MACV Team from Tanh Canh.
Took one hit, the engine quit resulting in a forced landing in an NVA controlled area. Aircraft abandoned for days then destroyed.
Destroyed by SA-7 while assisting elements of F/4 rescue two AF pilots and one AF FAC.  During the mission, a second Huey was shot down
Material failure of a blade retaining pin. 5 crewmen and 27 soldiers were lost.
Shot down by an SA-7 missile at 1233 hours over An Loc.
Shot down with SA-7 over An Loc
Cyclic controls shot out near Kontum on an ARVN resupply mission. Aircraft landed hard and burned.
Was C&C for a VR around Phu My-LZ Crystal, shot down while taking off during rescue of LOH crew. All were rescued.
During a VR around Phu My-LZ Crystal, shot down by an SA-7. Tail boom destroyed. Crew rescued.
Shot down leaving LZ. Crew rescued. Aircraft abandoned due to tactica situation.
Shot down with .51 cal.
Shot down by an SA-7 missile over An Loc.
Shot down on the 19th east of the highway running north out of Kontum. Crew was rescued even though both were serviously wounded.
Brand-new '20' ship shot down near Bong Son.
Forced down by bad weather in NVA territory.  Last air crew rescured by 37 ARRS out of Danang.  Helicopter never recovered.
Crashed into the sea on approach to USS HANCOCK after having flown a log and exhausting night SAR.
